(40, 13, 47, 62, 4, 1, 6, 'gathered of every kind', 'Gathering and Discernment Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment in gathering, as the net collects every kind, paralleling the call to test spirits to discern truth from falsehood. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing what is of God amidst a diverse array.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 47, 40, 13, 26, 30, 'gathered of every kind', 'Connection of Harvest Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering process at harvest time. The net in Matthew 13:47 and the reaping of wheat and tares in Matthew 13:26-30 illustrate the sorting of good and bad elements within the kingdom of heaven.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 47, 41, 1, 17, 17, 'gathered of every kind', 'Fishing for Souls', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of gathering, with the net in Matthew symbolizing the collection of people, while Mark speaks of becoming ''fishers of men.'' This connection highlights the transformative mission of Jesus in relation to the kingdom of heaven.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 48, 40, 13, 30, 30, 'gathered the good into vessels', 'Harvest and Separation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the process of gathering and separating. In Matthew 13:48, the good are gathered into vessels while the bad are cast away, paralleling the separation of wheat and tares in Matthew 13:30.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 48, 40, 3, 12, 12, 'gathered the good into vessels', 'Purging and Gathering Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the act of gathering good while discarding the bad. This connection highlights the theme of separation between valuable and worthless elements.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 48, 40, 13, 40, 43, 'gathered the good into vessels', 'Gathering of the Good and Bad', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of good and bad elements, with the good being preserved and the bad discarded. This connection highlights the theme of judgment and separation at the end of the world.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 49, 66, 20, 12, 15, 'sever the wicked from among the just', 'Judgment and Separation of the Wicked', 'Both passages emphasize the judgment of individuals based on their works and the separation of the wicked from the just. Matthew speaks of angels severing the wicked from the just, while Revelation describes the dead being judged and the wicked being cast into the lake of fire.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 49, 40, 13, 39, 39, 'the end of the world', 'Connection of End Times and Angels', 'Both passages emphasize the role of angels at the end of the world, highlighting their function in separating the wicked from the just. This connection illustrates a consistent theme of divine judgment and the final harvest.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 49, 40, 24, 31, 31, 'the angels shall come forth', 'Angels and Gathering of the Elect', 'Both passages emphasize the role of angels in gathering and separating individuals at the end of the world. Matthew 13:49 speaks of angels severing the wicked from the just, while Matthew 24:31 describes angels gathering the elect.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 49, 40, 22, 12, 14, 'the wicked from among the just', 'Separation of the Wicked', 'Both passages emphasize the separation of the wicked from the just. In Matthew 13:49, angels sever the wicked, while in Matthew 22:13, the unworthy are cast into outer darkness, illustrating a similar theme of judgment and exclusion.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 49, 40, 25, 5, 12, 'the wicked from among the just', 'Separation of the Just and Wicked', 'Both passages emphasize the separation of individuals based on their readiness and righteousness. In Matthew 13:49, the angels sever the wicked from the just, while in Matthew 25:5-12, the wise virgins are admitted to the marriage, and the foolish are excluded.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 49, 53, 1, 7, 10, 'the angels shall come forth', 'Judgment and Separation Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the role of angels in executing divine judgment at the end of the world. Matthew speaks of angels severing the wicked from the just, while 2 Thessalonians describes angels taking vengeance on those who do not obey the gospel.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 50, 40, 8, 12, 12, 'there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth', 'Connection of Judgment Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of exclusion from the kingdom, depicting a place of suffering characterized by ''wailing and gnashing of teeth.'' This connection highlights the severity of judgment faced by those cast out.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 50, 40, 13, 42, 42, 'there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth', 'Connection of Judgment Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of being cast into a furnace of fire, highlighting the theme of judgment. The phrase ''there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth'' reinforces the severity of this judgment in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 50, 42, 13, 27, 28, 'there shall be wailing and gnashing of teeth', 'Weeping and Gnashing of Teeth', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''weeping and gnashing of teeth'' as a consequence for those excluded from the kingdom of God. This connection highlights the theme of judgment and separation from the righteous.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 50, 66, 14, 10, 11, 'furnace of fire', 'Connection of Eternal Torment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of torment by fire, indicating a severe consequence for those who oppose God. The imagery of fire and the absence of rest in Revelation parallels the ''furnace of fire'' and ''wailing and gnashing of teeth'' in Matthew.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 50, 66, 16, 10, 11, 'gnashing of teeth', 'Connection of Suffering and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize intense suffering and anguish. The ''gnashing of teeth'' in Matthew parallels the ''gnawed their tongues for pain'' in Revelation, highlighting the torment faced by those judged.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 51, 40, 13, 11, 11, 'Have ye understood all these things?', 'Understanding the Mysteries', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of understanding the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven. In Matthew 13:51, the disciples affirm their understanding, while Matthew 13:11 highlights that this understanding is given specifically to them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 51, 40, 13, 19, 19, 'understood all these things', 'Understanding the Word of the Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding in relation to the word of the kingdom. In Matthew 13:51, the disciples affirm their understanding, while in Matthew 13:19, a lack of understanding leads to the loss of the word sown in the heart.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 51, 41, 4, 34, 34, 'Have ye understood all these things?', 'Understanding Jesus'' Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the understanding of Jesus'' teachings. In Matthew, the disciples affirm their comprehension, while in Mark, Jesus explains his parables to them when alone, suggesting a deeper understanding is necessary.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 51, 41, 7, 18, 18, 'understood all these things', 'Understanding and Perception', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus asks if they have understood, while in Mark, he questions their perception, emphasizing the importance of comprehension in spiritual matters.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 51, 42, 9, 44, 45, 'understood all these things', 'Understanding Jesus'' Teachings', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding Jesus'' teachings. In Matthew, the disciples affirm their understanding, while in Luke, they fail to comprehend his message about his impending suffering.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 51, 44, 8, 30, 31, NULL, 'Understanding Scripture''s Meaning', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding scripture. In both passages, the question of comprehension is central, with Jesus asking if his disciples understand and Philip inquiring if the eunuch understands what he reads.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 51, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'understood all these things', 'Understanding of Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding in both passages. In Matthew, the disciples affirm their understanding of Jesus'' teachings, while in 1 John, it is stated that the Son of God gives believers understanding to know the true God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 52, 62, 2, 7, 8, 'things new and old', 'Old and New Commandments', 'This connection highlights the interplay between old and new teachings. Both passages emphasize the importance of bringing forth wisdom that is both ancient and contemporary, reflecting a continuity in the message of the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 52, 55, 3, 16, 17, 'instructed unto the kingdom of heaven', 'Connection of Instruction and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being instructed and equipped for good works. Matthew highlights the role of the scribe in bringing forth treasures, while 2 Timothy speaks of scripture''s role in instruction and preparation for righteousness.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 52, 56, 1, 9, 9, 'things new and old', 'Connection of Teaching and Doctrine', 'This connection highlights the role of teaching in both passages. Matthew emphasizes the importance of bringing forth ''things new and old,'' while Titus stresses holding fast to ''the faithful word'' to instruct others.', 'theme', 0.37, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 52, 40, 12, 35, 35, 'bringeth forth out of his treasure', 'Connection of Treasure Concepts', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''treasure'' as a source of good or evil outcomes. Matthew 13:52 speaks of bringing forth ''things new and old'' from one''s treasure, while Matthew 12:35 contrasts the good and evil treasures of the heart.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 52, 47, 3, 4, 6, 'things new and old', 'Connection of New and Old', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the ''new'' and ''old'' teachings. Both passages emphasize the importance of being instructed and able ministers, focusing on the spirit rather than the letter.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 13, 52, 56, 2, 6, 7, 'things new and old', 'Connection of Good Works and Instruction', 'This connection highlights the importance of being instructed and producing good works. Both passages emphasize the role of teaching and exemplifying virtues in the community.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
